Package: sillylogic
Title: Emote via Logical Constants
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Benjamin", "Nutter", email = "nutter@battelle.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Inspired by a Twitter discussion, alternate representations of \code{TRUE}
  and \code{FALSE} are provided.  These may be used to place a little levity in the
  code, most famously for \code{stringsAsFactors=FALSE}.
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
Suggests: testthat
